[B][SIZE=5]Visual Improvements[/SIZE][/B]<br>
V6.2 also sees some pretty major improvements to the visual fidelity of the map.  Whilst often subtle, these changes help make Paralake look the best it ever has.  Some of the most notable changes include:
<br>
<br>

[LIST]
[*]Brand new water shaders, including directional flow, foam, and improved reflections
[*]A rework of the maps lighting to increase visual depth and contrast
[*]Improved shading on many real and fake buildings allowing for them to recieve/cast shadows on each other, as well as from other smaller props
[*]An increase in lightmap resolution accross the entire map, allowing for more detailed and realsitic shadows
[*]New sprites attached to many exterior lights, emulating the look of fog at night
[*]Both road street lights and vintage street lights switch to and off texture during the day
[*]New particles ported from Paralake V6 Night
[*]Updated many exterior ground textures to add a layer of grime/vairiation
[*]Fuel prices (including tax) now display on the Gas Station signs
[/LIST]
<br>
<br>

