[B][SIZE=7][U]Vanity Store[/U][/SIZE][/B]<br>
In this update, we are introducing the PERPHeads Vanity Store.  This new shop, accessable via !store or by clicking on a Premium Token in your inventory, is a new way to customize and express yourself in the game, whilst also supporting the server's continued upkeep and development.  The items sold in the Vanity Store will be aesthetic only, nothing that will give a player a gameplay advantage over another.
<br>
<br>

The Vanity Store brings with it a new currency, which we are calling Credits which you obtain by converting Premium Tokens.  1 Premium Token is worth 100 Credits
<br>
<br>

[CENTER][IMG size="2048x1152"]https://files.perpheads.com/dMAfsQujcwlzYgtn.jpg[/IMG][/CENTER]
<br>
<br>

As of today, the following items options are available in the Vanity Store:
<br>
<br>

[LIST]
[*][B]Redeem Premium:[/B]  From today onwards, this will be how you use a Premium Token to redeem premium for your account.
[*][B]Custom License Plate:[/B]  Similar to the old system at City Hall, this will let you purchase custom license plates for use on your vehicles.
[*][B]Custom Bank Number:[/B]  This will let you purchase a custom bank number for use in your in-game transactions.
[*][B]Storage Chest Skins:[/B]  These are custom skins/models for your storage chest in properties.  Once purchased you own it perminantly and can apply it whenever you like.
[*][B]Heterochromia:[/B]  This unlocks the ability for you to set mismatching eye colours at the Plastic Surgery NPC in the Hospital.
[*][B]Custom Badge Number:[/B]  This allows you to purchase a new PLPD Badge Number.
[*][B]Custom Phone Number:[/B]  This allows you to purchase a new custom phone number.
[*][B]Workbench Skins:[/B]  These are custom skins/models for your workbench.  Once purchased you own it perminantly and can apply it whenever you like.
[*][B]Skin Changer Tool:[/B]  This lets you purchase skin changer tools.  More information on this is below.
[/LIST]
<br>
<br>

[I][B]There is an FAQ section regarding the new Vanity Store at the end of this post.[/B][/I]
<br>
<br>

[CENTER][IMG size="1920x56"]https://files.perpheads.com/jaWteiRlDgekuOlm.png[/IMG][/CENTER]
<br>
<br>

[B][SIZE=7][U]Skin Changer Tool[/U][/SIZE][/B]<br>
This new item allows you to change the skin and colour of some props in game.  The tool is available to purchase from the Vanity Store, costing 10 Credits.
<br>
<br>

To use the tool, simply look at a prop that you wish to skin and click on the Skin Changer in your inventory.  If the prop has available customization options it will open a menu allowing you to change either the prop's skin, color, or both.  If used on lights, this tool will also allow you to change the colour of that light.
<br>
<br>

Each Skin Changer Tool is a single use item, but customized props are changed permanently (or until you customize them again).  Customized props are stored in your store/inventory as different vairients when you hover over them.
<br>
<br>

[CENTER][IMG width="459px" size="533x627"]https://files.perpheads.com/HVofGpv9ggOhmQJc.jpg[/IMG] [IMG size="543x354"]https://files.perpheads.com/2JojOQ6rijVhmfKG.jpg[/IMG][/CENTER]
<br>
<br>

You will be able to sell both Skin Changer Tools you have purchased, and props you have already skinned, in your shops in-game.
A full list of currently customizable props is available here, with more to be added in the future.
<br>
<br>

