Click the spoiler for a short list of frequently asked questions regarding the new Vanity Store.  If your question isn't in here please get in touch.
<br>
<br>

[SPOILER="Vanity Store FAQ"]
[B]Q:  Can I get a refund for something I purchased in the Vanity Store?
A: [/B] Unfortunatly, we are unable to give refunds for purchases in the Vanity Store, unless it is due to a license plate being denied (in this case the refund is automatic).  For more information, click [URL='https://store.perpheads.com/terms-of-service']here[/URL].
<br>
<br>

[B]Q:  Can I still sell Premium Tokens to other players?
A:[/B]  Yes!
<br>
<br>

[B]Q:  Can I sell Credits to other players?
A: [/B] No, once a Premium token has been converted into Credits, the Credits are locked to your account.
<br>
<br>

[B]Q:  Can I purchase credits without a Premium Token?
A:[/B]  No, you can currently only obtain Credits by converting a Premium Token.  This is done automatically on checkout, and any remaining Credits will be added to your Credit Balance.
<br>
<br>

[B]Q:  Will you be able to sell custom phone/badge/bank numbers?
A: [/B] No, once you buy a new number the old one gets returned to the pool for someone else to buy.  The exception is license plates, which work the same as they always have.
<br>
<br>

[B]Q:  Will it be more expensive to buy shorter license lates?
A: [/B] Yes, same as the old system, just with a different currency.
<br>
<br>

[B]Q:  Do Premium Tokens need to be in my inventory?
A:[/B]  No, the store will use Tokens from both your inventory and storage, but it will prioritise inventory first.
<br>
<br>

[B]Q:  Can I use colored spotlights in my base defence?
A: [/B] No, and the rules will be updated to reflect this shortly.
<br>
<br>

[B]Q:  Can someone purchase my randomly assigned badge number?
A:[/B]  As long as you don't free up that number by purchasing a new one, no.  You can only buy unowned badge numbers
[/SPOILER]